PASSENGER INFORMATION
1. Children
Children under two years of age not occupying separate seats
carried free of charge on Flights
905/3, 671/2 and
On all other routes, children under two years of age will be
charged at 1/10th of the published adult fare but they shall
not occupy separate seats.
Children who have reached their second birthday but have
not yet reached twelfth will be charged 50% of the publish-
ed adult fare.
Free Baggage Allowance
Free baggage allowance for each adult or hal -fare passenger
on all international flights shall be lim ted to 66 pounds (30
kilograms); on all domestic flights inside China, 33 pounds
(15 kilograms). For children under two years of age, there
is no free baggage allowance.
A passenger may also
sonally carry free of charge unchecked hand baggage of not
more than three kilograms.

Reservations
Reservations on all CNAC and connecting services can be
made at any CNAC Office.
Hotel accommodation ard ground
transportation at destination can be arranged upon request
prior to departure.
Cancellations
CNAC will not guarantee any refund for a cancellation or de-
ferment at short notice.
Passengers are therefore requested
to notify us at the earliest moment if any cancellation or de-
ferment is unavoidable.
Stop-overs
Passengers may break their journey at one or more places en
route with the benefit of the through fare, provided arrange-
ments are made at the time of reservation.
Expenses at such
stop-overs, however, will be for the passenger's account.
